This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it discusses the use of evolutionary techniques, specifically novelty search, in coevolutionary systems. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves the development of algorithms for evolving solutions. The Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper evaluates the proposed methods in a predator-prey pursuit task. Finally, the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper discusses the use of coevolutionary systems to evolve solutions.
